<TITLE> 2 to die for murder in Gopalganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, May 4 (bdnews24.com)  A court in Gopalganj has sentenced two persons to death including the husband for killing his wife. Gopalganj District and Session' Judge Khandakar Kamal Uzzaman delivered the verdict on Tuesday. The convicts are husband Imdadul Huq Sarder, 25, and Farid Gazi, 26, his associate. They were also fined Tk 20,000 each. Another accused in the case was released as the allegations against him could not be proved. According to the case, on Aug 21, 2009 Imdadul and Farid killed Josna Begum, 17, and severed her head from the body. They then dumped the headless body in a jute field and tossed the head into the Madhumati river. Police recovered the body on the following day. The incident took place in Fuckra village of Kashiani upazila. A case was filed on Aug 22 with Kashiani Police Station in this connection. Sub Inspector Ibrahim Patwary, investigation officer on the case, submitted the charge sheet against three, one of whom was acquitted by the court. bdnews
